<div id="review_195157207" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/195157207" />
    <a title="Liz Young" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5972952-liz-young"><img alt="Liz Young" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/195157207?book_show_action=true">Aug 06, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Liz Young" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Liz Young" href="/user/show/5972952-liz-young">Liz Young</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer195157207" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11565055361266405">There have been several books in my life which have altered my perspective on the world, and my place in it. This is one of them. There are some stories which, fact or fiction, just hit you in some core part of the soul. The idea that this story is real adds to the kick. <br/><br/><br/><br/>Nando&apos;s story of survival is no doubt one jaded by time and perspective. I wonder how many of the other survivors of this ordeal has read this work, and what their commentaries are. I wonder how other survivors of other such tra</span>
  <span id="freeText11565055361266405" style="display:none">There have been several books in my life which have altered my perspective on the world, and my place in it. This is one of them. There are some stories which, fact or fiction, just hit you in some core part of the soul. The idea that this story is real adds to the kick. <br /><br /><br /><br />Nando's story of survival is no doubt one jaded by time and perspective. I wonder how many of the other survivors of this ordeal has read this work, and what their commentaries are. I wonder how other survivors of other such tragedies feel about Nando's views and thoughts since his escape. Mostly, though, I am just in awe of his journey. <br /><br /><br /><br />It sure makes you realise how lucky you are.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11565055361266405" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


