<div id="review_3463169401" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3463169401" />
    <a title="Jaime" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/51482171-jaime"><img alt="Jaime" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1609797010p2/51482171.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3463169401?book_show_action=true">Aug 27, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jaime" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jaime" href="/user/show/51482171-jaime">Jaime</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3463169401" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13672258491203625277">My book of the year so far.... A story most will know - the Uruguayan rugby team who crashed high in the Andes and the story of how 16 survived. Those who have read Alive, or seen the film of the same name, will know of the extreme measures they had to take to survive, but this book is not really about that, or the survival, but about the emotions of one man. Alive is effectively a day by day documentary retelling the events, intense spirit, bravery, and determination. This is a book about one m</span>
  <span id="freeText13672258491203625277" style="display:none">My book of the year so far.... A story most will know - the Uruguayan rugby team who crashed high in the Andes and the story of how 16 survived. Those who have read Alive, or seen the film of the same name, will know of the extreme measures they had to take to survive, but this book is not really about that, or the survival, but about the emotions of one man. Alive is effectively a day by day documentary retelling the events, intense spirit, bravery, and determination. This is a book about one man’s love, for his friends, for his family, and for his family yet to be. And how that saved him, and changed his live. Genuinely one of the most beautiful books I have ever read... And probably as close to the meaning of life as you are ever likely to get. As Nando says so eloquently, “the opposite of death is not life, the opposite of death, is love”. His story leaves you in no doubt about why that is so true to him, but also why it should be so true to all of us. I cannot recommend this book more highly... And for those of you with audible membership, it’s also a splendid audio book, made even more powerful by the author’s reading of the opening and closing chapters. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13672258491203625277" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


