<span id="freeTextContainer15367966235918272501">From page 1 to the end, Parrado unapologetically told his story of survival. Recounting episodes of bravery, humility, worry, and fear, Parrado takes the reader through his journey in the Andes. While reading his accounts it’s impossible not to ponder the horrific realities the survivors experienced, yet Parrado continued to find the silver lining behind it all. I can’t help but notice parallels between Parrado’s narrative throughout this book and the biggest lesson the Miracle in the Andes taug</span>
  <span id="freeText15367966235918272501" style="display:none">From page 1 to the end, Parrado unapologetically told his story of survival. Recounting episodes of bravery, humility, worry, and fear, Parrado takes the reader through his journey in the Andes. While reading his accounts it’s impossible not to ponder the horrific realities the survivors experienced, yet Parrado continued to find the silver lining behind it all. I can’t help but notice parallels between Parrado’s narrative throughout this book and the biggest lesson the Miracle in the Andes taught him. The opposite of dark is light and “the opposite of death is love”. </span>
